<TITLE> More disabled students to get stipend </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, December 2 (bdnews24.com) Government stipends will cover 832 more disabled students than last year, said a special aide Tuesday. "We also have plans to raise the stipends for disabled students at the university level," said MA Malek, special assistant to the chief adviser for social welfare, at a press conference. The government is also planning to undertake a survey to get an accurate idea of the number of disabled people in the country, he said. According to a UN survey, ten per cent population of the country is disabled and on that account, the number may be around 50 lakh, said Dr Kamal Abdul Naser, director general of the social welfare departmentalso present at the press brief being held ahead of the International Day for the Disabled on Wednesday. Last year, Tk 5 crore was allotted for stipends to disabled students, which has been raised this year to Tk 6 crore, said Malek. With the additional 832 recipients, a total of 13,041 persons will now get government help, he added. "The lowest stipend has also been increased from Tk 220 to Tk 250," said Malek. The International Day for Persons with Disabilities is observed worldwide on Dec 3. The theme this year is: Dignity and justice for all. bdnew
